                      "explainText": "Set the action performed when the middle mouse button is clicked on the window title:\n\n\"Toggle to header\" (\"toggle_shade\") – minimize the window to the header. By double-clicking, the window expands back;\n\n\"Full screen\" (\"toggle_maximize\") — expand the window to full screen or restore the original size;\n\n\"Stretch vertically\" (\"toggle_maximize_vertically\") — expand the window vertically without changing its width;\n\n\"Stretch horizontally\" (\"toggle_maximize_vertically\") — expand the window horizontally without changing its height;\n\n\"Minimize\" — minimize the window;\n\n\"Show menu\" (\"menu\") – show the window menu;\n\n\"Push\" (\"lower\") – place a window under others;\n\n\"Do nothing\" (\"none\") — do not perform any action;\n\n\"Last action\" (\"last\") – repeat the previous action.\n\nThe \"Block\" option — (available only for machine policy) prevents the user from changing this setting. Blocking a policy makes it a priority over a similar policy for the user.",
